labels-0.0.0: Declare and access tuple fields with labels

Safe HaskellNone
LanguageHaskell2010

Labels.Internal

Contents

  • Orphan instances

Description

This module provides a way to name the fields in a regular Haskell tuple and then look them up later, statically.

Synopsis

  • data label := value = KnownSymbol label => (Proxy label) := value
  • class Has label value record | label record -> value where
    • modify :: Has label value record => Proxy label -> (value -> value) -> record -> record
    • class Cons label value record where
      • type Consed label value record

    Documentation

    data label := value infix 6 Source #

    Field named l labels value of type t. Example: (#name := "Chris") :: ("name" := String)

    Constructors

    KnownSymbol label => (Proxy label) := value infix 6
